Address: Lot 3/2412 Murray Valley Hwy Cudgewa VIC 3705
Description:
RED GUM RISE
BUILD YOUR DREAMS
Red Gum Rise is a rural selection of lifestyle properties that will energise your imagination to enable a lifestyle that encapsulates environmental, community and personal living in the North East Victoria. From the selections overlooking the valleys to the Australian Alps, the choice is now in your hands.
Red Gum rise is located in an ideal location with ample north and east facing vistas, from first light in the morning breaking over the alps to the setting sun to your west, Red Gum Rise has the site to offer solar passive living.
The local mountains protect you from harsh winds and the high snow peaks offering alpine like conditions cooling through-out the winter months.
Situated on the Murray Valley Highway, Red Gum Rise is on the edge of the Cudgewa Village, 12 kilometers west of Corryong, 120 Kilometres from Albury/Wodonga and midway between Sydney and Melbourne.
Corryong is close to the Burrowa-Pine Mountain National Park and the massive Alpine National Park.

Description:
"The Getaway Block"
"The Getaway Block"
Incredible Lifestyle/Farm with Nariel Creek Frontage
This is the ultimate camping, hunting, fishing retreat on approximately 150 acres in the most beautiful part of the Upper Murray, the Nariel Valley.
The farm includes 80 acres of fertile creek flats, consisting mainly perennial pastures of rye/clover which has had a recent application of lime. Carrying approximately 30 cows and calves "The Getaway Block" has a secure never failing water supply through many spring fed dams and soaks, high rainfall area and a small frontage to the Nariel Creek.
The farm includes a quality set of steel cattle yards with ramp and head bail, excellent boundary fencing to main road on both sides and approximately 1,500 meters of new internal post and wire fencing. There are two sheds on this fantastic farm; one an old piggery approximately 25 meters x 15 meters with an Aluminium Roof, the other shed located next to the yards with power connected is approximately 15 meters x 15 meters.
The balance of the farm includes rising hill country and bush with an abundance of wildlife including dear, emus and birdlife. An extremely serene and peaceful part of Australia to relax on weekends in your very own rustic camping area. Fully equipped with a solar hot water shower and caravan, sit back by the warm fire place and enjoy the most incredible view towards the mountains, which often have a dusting of snow.
Only 1 hour and 20 minutes from Wodonga & 25 minutes from Corryong, the farm would qualify for a planning permit (STCA). There are many quality home sites and power is available (connected) at the front gate.
Inspections are strictly by appointment.

Description:
Sensational Sustainability
It takes a giant leap to move from a big city and a fulltime job, or does it make sense to get something back in your life that you are missing. In 1991 this happened with the current owners, deciding on a life changing move that is said to have added years onto their lives.
Now it is your chance to own this piece of paradise on the Scrubby Creek.
You will find an amazing parcel of land being approx. 93 acres offering permanent creek frontage, landscaped gardens, native bushland and wetlands, all in one location. The grounds surrounding the residence offer a holistic and complete package of fruit trees and vegetable gardens to live off the land. With native birds and animals living on the property, your days are filled with permanent entertainment and intrigue.
The residence and its surrounding features are a statement to environmentally sustainable living. Having four pods joined by the engine room, being the kitchen/living room with a cellar connected to the creek. The residence is cooled by passive air from the stream which flows at your doorstep.
Four bedrooms offer plenty of options for guests or spaces to work from home. Having been connected to the internet, you have access to the world.

Description:
"Woollybutt"
“Woollybut” is situated in the highly regarded Upper Murray district on the eastern side of the Murray Valley Highway to the south west of the township of Corryong. The property is approximately 120 kilometres east of Wodonga and less than six kilometres south-west of Corryong.
“Woollybutt” presents as a recreational block of approximately 128.6 hectares (or 317.6 acres) for the fishing, camping, hunting, walking and riding enthusiasts providing seclusion and privacy as a true “bush escape”.
Set amongst the beautiful and picturesque Victorian High Country in the Upper Murray district with its stunning scenery and rolling pastures, “Woollybutt” provides more than a kilometre of frontage to the permanent Nariel Creek and boasts magnificent and uninterrupted views across the district from the elevated areas.
Idyllic camping sites are provided along the banks of the Nariel Creek for the camping enthusiast. For the fishing enthusiast, the Nariel Creek has a reputation as one of the best trout fishing streams in north east Victoria.
Substantial areas of bush country are also provided for the hunting enthusiast, while bushwalkers, horse riders, mountain bike riders and motorbike riders will enjoy exploring the more rugged terrain of “Woollybutt” with the breathtaking views provided from the elevated areas.
A converted 20’ shipping container is provided for storage to allow equipment to be held on site. The modified shipping container also has a pitched roof to allow for the collection of rainwater if required.
“Woollybutt” presents as an exciting opportunity to the recreational buyer seeking a “bush escape” in a private and secluded setting in the beautiful and picturesque Victorian High Country.
“Woollybutt” supports many recreational pursuits including: camping, fishing, hunting, bushwalking, horse riding, mountain bike riding and motorbike riding.
For further information please contact Mike Weller, Rural Sales Manager on 040 663 041. Inspections are strictly by appointment only.

Address: Proposed Lot 13 Evans Road Cudgewa VIC 3705
Description:
WABBA DOWNS
"Wabba Downs" is a well maintained 419 acre property. One of the best in the district. Capable of running approx. 165 breeder cattle. The property consists of gentle undulating hills which have been subdivided into 13 main paddocks with water for easy management. The steeper hill country is divided into 2 paddocks ideal for winter and summer grazing.
Good Super history and effective weed control programmes have been implemented for rotational grazing or set stocking, the choice is yours. The fencing is in good condition and the property provides ample water wth 12 spring fed and run off dams. Amazing views from various parts of the property are stunning.
The brick veneer home on the property consists of 3 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, spacious living area, kitchen and a large undercover entertaining area, with a built in bbq.
Additional improvements include two large hay sheds, large machinery shed with power and decommissioned dairy/cattle yards.
The property is for sale by Tender closing 4th November 2016. Please contact agent for inspection and tender package.

Description:
'UP THE CREEK' - 81.82 Hectares - 202.18 Acres
This versatile property is 16km from Corryong and fronts the Thougla Creek. It has sealed road access with two gateways to the road, stunning views down the Thougla Valley and school bus past the gate. Approximately 60% of this undulating to hilly block is clear, with the remainder bush which abounds with wildlife including deer. There are good access tracks throughout and water is supplied by spring fed dams and the Thougla Creek. This is a great add-on block for running heifers, a weekender or the perfect site for your dream build.
Property Code: 973

Description:
Magnificent Nariel Valley. Ideal weekender close to Scrubby Creek and Nariel Creek.
Situated in the heart of the beautiful Nariel Valley this small 1 acres (4,000m2) allotment is close to Nariel Creek, Scrubby Creek and the beautiful bush with all popular recreational pursuits.
The older style fibro home comprises three (3) bedrooms, one with built in robe. Two (2) bathrooms. Open plan living with spacious kitchen, gas cooking, overhead fans, large walk in pantry. The large lounge has a slow combustion heater. Solar heating with electric booster for hot water. A double carport at side of home makes for easy car accommodation.
Shedding is older style with a wood shed, 3 bay machinery shed and store room, chook yard plus miscellaneous shedding. A free standing bungalow is ideal for extra accommodation or home office.
Water is via rainwater 27,500 litres plus permanent Scrubby Creek - Stock and Domestic Licence.
The established surrounds include vegetable garden, deciduous trees, a variety of fruit trees, rhododendrons and camellias plus many other varieties.
Insights: 2955 Benambra-corryong Road, Nariel Valley VIC 3707 was last sold in 2015.

Description:
UPPER MURRAY DISTRICT - Lot 1 - 11.86 Acres Lot 2 - 86 Acres
Two lifestyle blocks of Land located in the picturesque Upper Murray District, located 8km to Cudgewa, 22km to Corryong & 118km to Wodonga.
LOT 1: 'The Creek' 4.8 Ha - 11.86 Acres of prime Cudgewa Creek Flats, superb fishing spot with the opportunity to run a few head of cattle, mature trees providing good shade & shelter, fenced into one paddock with great access to the Cudgewa Creek.
LOT 2: 'The Hill' 34.8 Ha - 86 Acres of prime grazing country with fertile flats through to gently undulating grazing country, established trees and fenced into one paddock, great views overlooking the Cudgewa creek flats.
For sale by Expressions Of Interest, with the option to purchase individually, or both blocks, closing Friday May the 8th at 5:00pm, 2015.
